trend_summary: Built-up area grows steadily along the main highway: new cul-de-sac subdivisions and small commercial nodes appear, while tree cover recedes and open fields fragment. Despite expansion, structures remain low-rise and dispersed; no dense core forms. The landscape therefore evolves into a moderately intensified, car-oriented suburban belt with gradual outward growth.
notable_changes: Several new residential subdivisions infill forested lots along the highway corridor.
Commercial/industrial rooftops emerge around the northeastern highway interchange.
Primary highway appears widened and supplemented by additional access roads and loops.
Contiguous woodland patches shrink noticeably, especially in the west and southeast.
Some former open or agricultural fields convert to housing, reducing undeveloped land.
